getEntry

public Collection<String> getEntry(String word)
This method implements the interface STTaggerDictionary by delegating to getEntry(String, int) (see below).

Specified by:
getEntry in interface STTaggerDictionary
Parameters:
word - A String representing a particular grammatical type.
Returns:
A Collection containing supertags (CCG lexical categories) seen with the particular grammatical type `key'. Returns null if that word was not seen in the corpus or (if the implementing class has a frequency cut-off) if that type's token frequency was not high enough.

getEntry

public Collection<String> getEntry(String word,
                                   int freq)
A method for getting the dictionary entry for a particular String word, only if that word appears at least `freq' times in the corpus.

Parameters:
key - A String representing a particular word.
freq - An int specifying the number of times a word should have occured before it is returned.
Returns:
A String[] containing all supertags (CCG lexical categories) seen with the specified word. Returns null if the word does not appear at least `freq' times in the corpus from which the dictionary was created or if the word does not appear at all. (N.B. Passing in an int `freq' value of zero will elicit the same behavior as passing in a `freq' value of 1.)
